In a former version of the Encoder.java class we can find this code.

## Previous versions
```
// Append ECI segment if applicable
    if (mode == Mode.BYTE && (hasEncodingHint || !DEFAULT_BYTE_MODE_ENCODING.equals(encoding))) {
      CharacterSetECI eci = CharacterSetECI.getCharacterSetECIByName(encoding);
      if (eci != null) {
        appendECI(eci, headerBits);
      }
    }
```

## Current version
```
// Append ECI segment if applicable
    if (mode == Mode.BYTE && hasEncodingHint) {
      CharacterSetECI eci = CharacterSetECI.getCharacterSetECIByName(encoding);
      if (eci != null) {
        appendECI(eci, headerBits);
      }
    }
```

The OR condition has been remove in newer versions.
I would like to humbly ask if it would be possible to have a stronger options like this one

## Proposal
`if (mode == Mode.BYTE && hasEncodingHint && !DEFAULT_BYTE_MODE_ENCODING.equals(encoding)) {`

The reason is that some old gun readers aren't prepared to read the ECI information and the read will fail if we add this ECI information (DATALOGIC QD2430 is a current example), some frameworks like jasper reports new versions are sending the Character encoding as hint ALWAYS, (i've warned them if so) but I hope it would be a stronger solution if you also check this.

Thanks for your awesome work.

